[Patient] What foods should I eat to help with my heart failure?
[Educator] Focus on fruits, veggies, whole grains, and lean proteins for heart health.
[Patient] Can you suggest affordable healthy food options in my neighborhood?
[Educator] Look for sales on fresh produce, canned beans, and whole grains for budget-friendly choices.
[Patient] How can I make sure I'm eating healthy on a tight budget?
[Educator] Plan meals ahead, buy in bulk, and use coupons to save money on nutritious foods.
[Patient] Are there any cultural dishes I can still enjoy while managing my heart failure?
[Educator] Yes, try healthier versions of traditional dishes like baked or grilled instead of fried.
[Patient] I struggle to cook, do you have any easy recipes to share?
[Educator] Try simple recipes like stir-fry veggies with lean protein or whole grain pasta with veggies.
[Patient] Are there any snacks I can have that won't worsen my heart failure?
[Educator] Opt for nuts, seeds, yogurt, or fruit for heart-healthy snacks between meals.
[Patient] How do I know if a food is good for my heart health?
[Educator] Look for foods low in sodium, saturated fats, and added sugars to support heart health.
[Patient] Can I still enjoy desserts while managing my heart failure?
[Educator] Yes, try fruit-based desserts or small portions of dark chocolate for a heart-healthy treat.